// This is a single line comment (using "//" before any line) anything succeeded by it for a single line will not be compiled and hence will not be executed either.
// By comments, I will be able to explain steps in my code.
// Below is the most basic program of any programming language which is printing Hello World !! in C language.
#include <stdio.h>   // tells compiler, for precompiled header files to be included/loaded. 
int main() // compiler starts execution fron main hence the control of flow of code starts from main, int is the data type of main() function which I will explain later.
{ 
  printf("Hello World !!"); //displays the content (here string due to being enclosed within double quotes, ("") ) which is passed into this function.
  return 0;
}
